==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suitable
<hw>Suit"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of suiting;
fitting; accordant; proper; becoming; agreeable; adapted; <as>as,
ornaments <ex>suitable</ex> to one's station; language <ex>suitable</ex>
for the subject</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Suit"a*ble*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos> -- <wf>Suit"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Proper; fitting; becoming; accordant; agreeable;
competent; correspondent; compatible; consonant; congruous;
consistent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suite</ent>⟦br⟧
